wikipedia_page.main: Major-General Sir William Digby Manifold Raeburn, KCVO, CB, DSO, MBE (1915–2001), commonly known as Sir Digby Raeburn, was a senior British Army officer. He was Resident Governor of the Tower of London from 1971 to 1979.

response: Sir Digby Raeburn (1915–2001), son of Sir Ernest Manifold Raeburn (1878–1922), second son of the first Baronet, was a Major-General in the Scots Guards and Governor of the Tower of London.
